Actors: Paul Hogan, Linda Kozlowski, John Meillon, David Gulpilil,

Directors: Peter Faiman
Writers: Paul Hogan, John Cornell, Ken Shadie
Studio: Paramount Home Entertainment
DVD Release Date: 14 Jan 2002
Run Time: 93 minutes
Synopsis:
Sue Charlton (Linda Kozlowski), a reporter for Newsday, travels Down 
Under to write a feature on Australia and its people. She gets a tip to 
visit a free-spirited bush ranger who was attacked by a crocodile--that 
he then killed with his bare hands. So Sue heads into the red sands and 
squalid swamps of Northern Territory outback to a tiny fly-blown burg 
called Walkabout Creek, where she is greeted by Wally (John Meillon) 
of Never-Never Safaris.
Producers: Jane Scott, John Cornell, Wayne Young
